----Original Message Follows----

From: Tea Lover Denise <jalecroy@...>

"Cultivate your own capabilities, your own style. Appreciate the
members of your family for who they are, even though their outlook or
style may be miles different from yours. Rabbits don't fly. Eagles
don't swim. Ducks look funny trying to climb. Squirrels don't have
feathers. Stop comparing. There's plenty of room in the forest."
-Chuck Swindoll
